rComments: Very good at inspiring class discussion yet keeping it on topic. Organized and knowledgeable - presents material well. Very friendly and thoughtful.

Professor Abell provides an environment for the free exchange of ideas. A rarity in university she does not penalize for differing opinions even if discriminatory or reward other opinions.  The grade you get is fair and just. I owe her a debt of gratitude for my education in Aboriginal persons and the law. Important exposure. Lucky to have her.

Terrible course.  Unhelpful comments on assignments, likely because she has not read the material.  Uses an outdated textbook.  Such a poor instructor that the exam question cited the wrong section from the criminal code.  Proceed with the expectation that you will learn very little.
She changed her mind a lot and was all over the place in class. It seemed like she put effort into the class, but was still unclear.

Avoid this professor if you can she makes her students do the lectures, she is not clear at times and changes her mind on a lot of the course work leaving the students confused and frustrated. She snaps at students as well so try not to do anything to offend her, forget going to the wash-room during class...
